1061
01:56:02,887 --> 01:56:06,118
It's missus Olson's young cuckoo!

1062
01:56:28,767 --> 01:56:30,917
Let's see how tough you are, Pelle.

1063
01:56:32,447 --> 01:56:33,846
To the sea with him!

1064
01:56:34,287 --> 01:56:35,845
Run cuckoo bird!
- Run!

1065
01:56:56,607 --> 01:56:58,563
Come on, let's see you dance!

1066
01:56:58,727 --> 01:57:01,366
Run cuckoo bird!

1067
01:57:07,527 --> 01:57:09,802
Come back to Sweden!

1068
01:57:09,967 --> 01:57:11,366
Go away, cuckoo bird!

1069
01:57:11,527 --> 01:57:13,483
Away, away, away, away!

1070
01:57:14,967 --> 01:57:17,606
Away, away, away!

1071
01:57:18,327 --> 01:57:21,956
Away, away, away. Come on!

1072
01:58:44,247 --> 01:58:45,885
Look! It's Captain Olson!

1073
01:59:14,447 --> 01:59:15,402
You're at home already.

1074
01:59:21,687 --> 01:59:24,076
Missus's Olson husband
has come home.

1075
02:00:36,767 --> 02:00:40,203
I will stay here forever...

1076
02:00:40,727 --> 02:00:42,638
...standing here like...

1077
02:00:43,367 --> 02:00:45,403
...a block of hay in the shed.

1078
02:00:46,487 --> 02:00:48,398
I was only looking for a home...

1079
02:00:49,167 --> 02:00:51,123
...to spend my old age.

1080
02:00:52,127 --> 02:00:55,403
I've found someone and I felt free.

1081
02:00:57,167 --> 02:00:58,486
Jesus!

1082
02:01:00,407 --> 02:01:02,045
Jesus, help!

1083
02:02:18,047 --> 02:02:20,436
What the hell is the point of crying?

1084
02:02:22,767 --> 02:02:24,883
I want you to meet my new sweetheart.

1085
02:02:27,247 --> 02:02:28,965
Here, Pelle.

1086
02:02:35,487 --> 02:02:36,966
I forgot...

1087
02:02:38,207 --> 02:02:40,926
...that you didn't this thing.
You're too fine.

1088
02:02:41,887 --> 02:02:44,003
It doesn't help going around...

1089
02:02:44,167 --> 02:02:45,998
...whimpering.

1090
02:02:52,007 --> 02:02:52,996
Papa!

1091
02:02:55,967 --> 02:02:57,878
It's sleepery.

1092
02:03:02,127 --> 02:03:04,197
This is a little devil.

1093
02:03:10,247 --> 02:03:11,680
You're crying?

1094
02:03:14,527 --> 02:03:16,438
If some do something to you...

1095
02:03:17,407 --> 02:03:21,400
...tell them that your father is
Lasse, from Tommelilla.

1096
02:03:21,727 --> 02:03:24,560
It's alright, your father is here.

1097
02:03:24,967 --> 02:03:28,323
And your father can stand
on his own two feet.

1098
02:03:32,807 --> 02:03:35,196
I'm going out to the big house.

1099
02:03:36,887 --> 02:03:38,718
Now the bastard is gonna...

1100
02:03:38,887 --> 02:03:40,878
...have to answer for all these years

1101
02:03:41,607 --> 02:03:43,916
We are going to have a
little talk with the missus.

1102
02:03:44,127 --> 02:03:45,685
I won't let you go out there!

1103
02:04:27,127 --> 02:04:28,276
Erik.

1104
02:04:30,127 --> 02:04:31,003
Erik.

1105
02:04:33,567 --> 02:04:34,443
Erik.

1106
02:04:36,807 --> 02:04:39,002
Spring is coming, that's
what papa says.

1107
02:04:40,807 --> 02:04:42,479
In the spring you'll be...

1108
02:04:43,527 --> 02:04:44,482
...a free man.

1109
02:04:46,447 --> 02:04:47,402
Think of it.

1110
02:04:49,687 --> 02:04:51,723
Then, we can leave this awful place.

1111
02:04:53,927 --> 02:04:55,724
And go out and conquer the world.

1112
02:05:19,727 --> 02:05:21,080
Pelle.

1113
02:05:23,167 --> 02:05:24,839
What is it they all talk about?

1114
02:05:25,447 --> 02:05:26,926
I wouldn't know.

1115
02:05:27,967 --> 02:05:29,559
You haven't heard anything?

1116
02:05:30,487 --> 02:05:33,957
Do you think I wanna go to class
so they can laugh at me some more?

1117
02:05:50,007 --> 02:05:52,726
I know I drink too much.

1118
02:05:54,047 --> 02:05:57,403
But it's difficult not to, when
you're heart is broken.

1119
02:06:02,967 --> 02:06:03,843
Pelle...

1120
02:06:05,287 --> 02:06:09,121
...if I promise you'll never again se
me the way I was yesterday...

1121
02:06:09,847 --> 02:06:11,758
...would you agree to go to school?

1122
02:06:11,927 --> 02:06:13,121
Tomorrow, Pelle?

1123
02:06:14,047 --> 02:06:15,321
Because if you don't...

1124
02:06:17,447 --> 02:06:18,675
...then they will force you.

1125
02:06:19,007 --> 02:06:21,396
There'll be a lot of trouble
with the authority.

1126
02:06:24,807 --> 02:06:26,877
Alright? Say yes.

1127
02:06:29,647 --> 02:06:32,286
10 times 10 is a hundred

1128
02:06:32,687 --> 02:06:36,077
100 times 10 is a thousand.

1129
02:06:36,247 --> 02:06:39,125
100 divided by 10 is 10.

1130
02:06:39,287 --> 02:06:42,120
1000 divided by 10 is 100.

1131
02:06:51,087 --> 02:06:52,281
Mister Freeze?

1132
02:06:52,567 --> 02:06:53,716
Mister Freeze.

1133
02:06:54,607 --> 02:06:55,722
He's asleep.

1134
02:06:56,007 --> 02:06:57,725
Mister Freeze, it's time.

1135
02:07:07,327 --> 02:07:08,282
Sir.

1136
02:07:09,247 --> 02:07:11,124
It's time to go home.

1137
02:08:14,487 --> 02:08:16,284
Pelle, where's your father?

1138
02:08:19,767 --> 02:08:20,961
Fooling around?

1139
02:08:23,687 --> 02:08:25,405
My father would be happy...

1140
02:08:25,567 --> 02:08:28,240
...to marry your father to captain
Olson's second wife.

1141
02:08:35,647 --> 02:08:37,558
Help papa! Help!

1142
02:08:41,727 --> 02:08:44,924
You scoundrel!
How dare you hit my son!

1143
02:08:45,887 --> 02:08:48,447
You're going to hear from
the authorities about this!

1144
02:08:54,487 --> 02:08:55,636
Pelle, Pelle, Pelle...

1145
02:08:55,807 --> 02:08:58,924
That was about the worst you
could do, hit the minister's son.

1146
02:08:59,807 --> 02:09:01,843
The town's minister.

1147
02:09:02,167 --> 02:09:04,317
He deserved it, I'm sure.

1148
02:09:04,487 --> 02:09:07,160
But still you shouldn't have done it.
What else did he do to you?

1149
02:09:07,647 --> 02:09:10,878
He said he could get you married
at boatsman Olson's second wife.

1150
02:09:12,167 --> 02:09:13,282
He did?

1151
02:09:15,047 --> 02:09:16,162
He did?

1152
02:09:17,287 --> 02:09:21,246
If I had him here,
I'd rip his innards out.

1153
02:09:21,647 --> 02:09:22,682
Do you feel revenged?

1154
02:09:22,887 --> 02:09:23,922
No, not really.

1155
02:09:24,647 --> 02:09:28,003
His father came and gave
what he deserved.

1156
02:09:28,167 --> 02:09:29,236
Revenge.

1157
02:09:30,687 --> 02:09:33,076
It's a bad situation.

1158
02:09:35,127 --> 02:09:37,277
And you don't intend to apologize?

1159
02:09:38,367 --> 02:09:40,085
No, no, you shouldn't.

1160
02:09:43,447 --> 02:09:46,564
Although maybe you should...
No, no.

1161
02:09:47,327 --> 02:09:48,806
You have to twist and turn...

1162
02:09:49,647 --> 02:09:51,285
...as the eel said in the frying pan.

1163
02:09:56,127 --> 02:09:58,482
We are very sorry to bother you...

1164
02:09:58,647 --> 02:10:01,207
We have no choice, but...

1165
02:10:01,607 --> 02:10:03,199
...to ask for your help.

1166
02:10:04,247 --> 02:10:06,044
Did you blow your nose properly?

1167
02:10:07,887 --> 02:10:10,003
We are very sorry to bother you, Sir.

1168
02:10:10,527 --> 02:10:11,721
I'm very sorry.

1169
02:10:18,767 --> 02:10:20,758
There's probably no one home.
- Let's go in.

1170
02:10:21,087 --> 02:10:22,725
We can't stand here all day.

1171
02:10:22,887 --> 02:10:25,879
Go first, if you think you
can handle this better.

1172
02:10:27,367 --> 02:10:28,595
Come in.

1173
02:10:30,327 --> 02:10:31,760
Good day.

1174
02:10:32,167 --> 02:10:33,566
Good day.

1175
02:10:35,687 --> 02:10:37,518
It's like this...

1176
02:10:39,647 --> 02:10:42,878
I hope the proprietor
be angry with us.

1177
02:10:44,847 --> 02:10:46,360
He won't be angry.

1178
02:10:51,247 --> 02:10:53,124
You must forgive us for coming here...

1179
02:10:53,287 --> 02:10:55,676
...to talk about something which
has nothing to do with the farm.

1180
02:10:56,407 --> 02:10:57,635
But...

1181
02:10:59,927 --> 02:11:01,883
...when the father's sins...

1182
02:11:02,567 --> 02:11:04,398
...are visited upon his son.

1183
02:11:05,447 --> 02:11:06,766
Then...

1184
02:11:06,927 --> 02:11:08,758
Then...
- Why are you standing?

1185
02:11:09,687 --> 02:11:10,756
Sit down, please.

1186
02:11:10,927 --> 02:11:12,679
Thank you.
- Why you haven't...

1187
02:11:12,847 --> 02:11:14,041
...offered them a sit, dear?

1188
02:11:22,687 --> 02:11:24,598
Thank you.
- What is it?

1189
02:11:25,607 --> 02:11:26,596
You need money?

1190
02:11:27,127 --> 02:11:28,924
No, it's...

1191
02:11:29,447 --> 02:11:30,880
Is just like a...

1192
02:11:31,527 --> 02:11:33,245
It's just that...

1193
02:11:36,927 --> 02:11:39,077
I hope that you won't be angry but...

1194
02:11:40,647 --> 02:11:42,046
...it's...

1195
02:11:42,927 --> 02:11:44,201
It's the boy.

1196
02:11:45,087 --> 02:11:46,805
They're going to send him away.

1197
02:11:47,447 --> 02:11:48,721
Send him away?
- Yes.

1198
02:11:48,927 --> 02:11:50,076
¿ What have you done?

1199
02:11:56,767 --> 02:11:58,564
I beat up the minister's son.

1200
02:11:59,887 --> 02:12:01,081
And why you did you do that?

1201
02:12:05,207 --> 02:12:07,437
Because he said evil
things about Lasse.

1202
02:12:08,967 --> 02:12:10,036
What did he say?

1203
02:12:11,367 --> 02:12:14,325
He called me...

1204
02:12:16,167 --> 02:12:18,920
He called me Mrs. Olson's plaything.

1205
02:12:19,527 --> 02:12:21,836
You know, the kids...

1206
02:12:27,527 --> 02:12:28,721
I was...

1207
02:12:29,807 --> 02:12:31,479
...Mrs. Olson's sweetheart.

1208
02:12:31,647 --> 02:12:33,842
Because everyone thought
she was a widow.

1209
02:12:36,367 --> 02:12:39,484
And other day her husband
came home from the sea.

1210
02:12:42,647 --> 02:12:43,762
Here.

1211
02:12:46,167 --> 02:12:49,398
And the boy made Pelle furious.
- Yes, unfortunately.

1212
02:12:50,327 --> 02:12:51,476
That's how it is.

1213
02:12:51,647 --> 02:12:52,477
With poor wretches...

1214
02:12:52,647 --> 02:12:54,717
...they're only there to be pecked at

1215
02:12:54,887 --> 02:12:57,447
Well, I prefer the bird that pecks
back and defends his nest...

1216
02:12:57,647 --> 02:12:59,444
...regardless of the poor it is.

1217
02:13:01,087 --> 02:13:04,716
I'll do what I can.
Don't worry about it anymore.

1218
02:13:04,967 --> 02:13:05,922
Thank you.

1219
02:13:08,127 --> 02:13:09,116
By the way.

1220
02:13:09,847 --> 02:13:12,042
My husband and I decided...

1221
02:13:12,287 --> 02:13:16,280
...the young assistant to
our foreman will be leaving.

1222
02:13:16,847 --> 02:13:20,601
Maybe Pelle would like to
become his replacement.

1223
02:13:25,247 --> 02:13:26,646
Thank you.

1224
02:13:26,927 --> 02:13:28,645
Say thank you.

1225
02:13:42,287 --> 02:13:45,757
Almost as if she thought
it was her own idea?

1226
02:13:46,047 --> 02:13:47,844
She thought, she thought it herself.

1227
02:13:49,967 --> 02:13:51,195
Your recognized this?

1228
02:13:51,847 --> 02:13:54,077
They're a bit big, but
we'll stuff them with papers.

1229
02:13:54,247 --> 02:13:55,600
Try them on.

1230
02:14:00,967 --> 02:14:03,322
I'll get some boot wax,
and they'll be like new.

1231
02:14:04,487 --> 02:14:06,159
Now let's have a look.

1232
02:14:10,927 --> 02:14:14,476
Stand up straight. I want
you stand very straight.

1233
02:14:14,687 --> 02:14:17,440
Shoulders back and
chin a little forward.

1234
02:14:17,607 --> 02:14:19,757
Not like that. Lift you chin a little

1235
02:14:19,927 --> 02:14:22,282
Now a sharp look in the eye.

1236
02:14:22,927 --> 02:14:24,997
You must command respect for yourself

1237
02:14:26,207 --> 02:14:28,675
The way you stand and the look
in your eye. That's what does it.

1238
02:14:32,327 --> 02:14:35,239
Let the others labour.
You give the orders.

1239
02:14:36,247 --> 02:14:37,600
You can't take tonight off!

1240
02:14:37,767 --> 02:14:39,280
Clean now the cow down!

1241
02:14:41,247 --> 02:14:42,282
And Pelle...

1242
02:14:43,447 --> 02:14:45,358
Maybe you'll get to eat
sunday dinner with the proprietor.

1243
02:14:45,527 --> 02:14:48,758
And have a napkin-ring
with your name on it.

1244
02:14:49,247 --> 02:14:50,566
Pelle Karlsson.

1245
02:15:02,727 --> 02:15:06,322
And who knows, Pelle. Maybe
one day you'll be the foreman.

1246
02:15:06,687 --> 02:15:10,475
I could tell you the way she
was thinking it was perfect.

1247
02:15:36,767 --> 02:15:38,041
Erik!

1248
02:15:42,447 --> 02:15:43,721
Erik!

1249
02:15:47,007 --> 02:15:48,520
Erik!

1250
02:15:49,327 --> 02:15:50,726
Wait for me!

1251
02:15:53,567 --> 02:15:54,886
Erik!

1252
02:16:19,687 --> 02:16:21,086
I don't want it.

1253
02:16:25,767 --> 02:16:27,485
We must leave here, papa.

1254
02:16:28,007 --> 02:16:29,486
Now.

1255
02:16:59,727 --> 02:17:00,762
It's Karna.

1256
02:17:00,927 --> 02:17:02,246
I get here in time.

1257
02:17:02,927 --> 02:17:05,043
I was afraid the foreman
and the missus would see me.

1258
02:17:06,327 --> 02:17:07,840
A gift for you.

1259
02:17:08,447 --> 02:17:09,926
It's a down quilt.

1260
02:17:10,167 --> 02:17:13,398
It'll keep you warm. No matter
where you end up in the world.

1261
02:17:14,647 --> 02:17:15,875
Bye, Gabriela.

1262
02:17:19,847 --> 02:17:21,041
Bye, Blanca.

1263
02:17:21,567 --> 02:17:23,046
You'll be a good girl.

1264
02:17:32,687 --> 02:17:34,166
Well, Aspasia.

1265
02:17:34,767 --> 02:17:36,564
Time to say goodbye to Pelle.

1266
02:17:37,127 --> 02:17:39,197
He is going up to see the world.

1267
02:17:47,127 --> 02:17:48,355
Papa.

1268
02:17:54,647 --> 02:17:55,921
What is it?

1269
02:18:03,767 --> 02:18:05,200
Can't we stay?

1270
02:18:32,687 --> 02:18:34,405
You'll have to go
without me, Pelle.

1271
02:18:35,927 --> 02:18:37,883
I don't have the strength anymore.

1272
02:18:38,167 --> 02:18:40,158
I'm too old. It's the reason.

1273
02:18:41,727 --> 02:18:43,126
Too old.

1274
02:18:45,367 --> 02:18:47,005
There's no future for an old man.

1275
02:18:50,727 --> 02:18:51,955
Do you understand that?

1276
02:19:11,247 --> 02:19:13,158
I'll make a bundle for you.

1277
02:19:13,807 --> 02:19:16,799
You can have 2 of
my shirts then you have 4.

1278
02:19:17,967 --> 02:19:19,844
Then one you're wearing is clean.

1279
02:19:20,647 --> 02:19:23,207
And remember: never wear
it more than two weeks...

1280
02:19:23,367 --> 02:19:25,722
...at a time, otherwise you
get bad name in town.

1281
02:19:26,007 --> 02:19:28,521
And change your socks
before they wear out.

1282
02:19:28,687 --> 02:19:30,643
Keep your clothes clean.
Keep your good name.

1283
02:19:30,847 --> 02:19:33,566
You save half the work and all shames

1284
02:19:38,447 --> 02:19:40,483
You can have my boots too.

1285
02:19:43,007 --> 02:19:44,998
They are a bit worn.

1286
02:19:48,727 --> 02:19:50,319
And here's the Bible.

1287
02:19:54,567 --> 02:19:56,603
Your mohter said
I was to give it to you...

1288
02:19:57,007 --> 02:19:59,202
...on the day she went
out to the world.

1289
02:20:28,727 --> 02:20:32,322
Next time we'll meet maybe
there'll be a proper home for you.

1290
02:20:37,287 --> 02:20:39,005
Say Karna goodbye.

1291
02:20:48,327 --> 02:20:49,726
Goodbye, papa.

1292
02:20:51,967 --> 02:20:52,843
Thank you.

